canonical:
  title: 曉行
  author: 金時習
  language: lzh
  text: 曉色照林墩鷄聲閙水村烟光凝野外露色遍郊原浩蕩乾坤𤄃蹉𧿶歲月奔衆人皆有托底事獨高鶱
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 曉行
  author: 金時習
  language: lzh
  text: 曉色照林墩。鷄聲閙水村。烟光凝野外。露色遍郊原。浩蕩乾坤𤄃。蹉𧿶歲月奔。衆人皆有托。底事獨高鶱。
korean:
  title: 효행
  author: 김시습
  language: kor
  text: |-
    새벽 빛은 수풀 언덕을 비추는데
    닭 소리는 강 마을에 시끄럽다
    연기 빛깔은 들 밖에 어리었고
    이슬 빛은 들판에 둘렀다
    호탕하게도 건곤은 너르나니
    미끄러지는 듯 세월은 내달린다
    사람들 모두 의탁할 데 있거니
    무슨 일로 나 혼자 높이 들려 있나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1420_010_0290&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Early Morning Journey
  author: Kim Si-seup
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Dawn's light breaks across the wooded hills,
    Rooster cries stir the riverside village awake.
    Smoke and mist gather beyond the fields,
    Dew spreads its sheen across the open plain.

    Vast and boundless, heaven and earth stretch wide,
    Yet time slips away like running water.
    All others find their place to rest upon—
    Why am I alone left suspended in the air?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The poem contrasts the natural world's expansiveness and order with the speaker's sense of dislocation and alienation from society.
  - key: ''
    value: '''Suspended in the air'' (高鶱) suggests both literal elevation and spiritual detachment—a state of wandering without purpose or refuge.'
